@node History "History"
@prev Future
@next Main

@{u}1.0@{uu}

First Release


@{u}1.1@{uu}

Bug fixed - @{b}DT2NI@{ub} worked only with picture.datatype for CGX (Thanks to @{b}Terry Fry@{ub})


@{u}1.2@{uu}

New features: process single file, give a default tool, create greyscaled icons, save tooltypes with information about picture

New arguments: DEFTOOL/K,GREY/K/N,NOTOOLTYPES/S

Now includes swedish catalog (Thanks to @{b}Torbjörn Aronsson@{ub})

Now works on 68000 (I think it should have worked on 68000 all the time)


@{u}1.3@{uu}

Bug fixed - if the SIZE/N got a too big number no error was printed.

Now @{b}DT2NI@{ub} does not replace existing normal icon images. If the argument NOTOOLTYPES is given existing tooltypes will be copied.

A second (inverted) image can be created to show the selected icon. Option: SECONDIMAGE/S

French catalog added (Thanks to @{b}Jerome Chesnot@{ub})

Norwegian catalog added (Thanks to @{b}Kim Roar Utsi@{ub})

Spanish catalog added (Thanks to @{b}Leopoldo Gomez@{ub})

Greek catalog added (Thanks to @{b}Elias Papanikolaou@{ub})


@{u}1.4@{uu}

Now HAM and EHB pictures are supported.

New feature: you can use the standard NewIcons palette (16 colors). Option: NICONCOLORS/S.

New feature: if you wish the black border that makes the icons square is not created. Option: NOBACKFILL/S.

I changed the code that maps the truecolor image down. Now it is a slower but more variable.

The chapter "Bugs" has changed to "Bugs and problems".

The beginning sentence in chapter "Future has changed" :)

The chapter "How does it work?" has been deleted.

Spanish guide added (Thanks to @{b}Leopoldo Gomez@{ub})

Now there is a support page:
  http://home.t-online.de/home/060334252-0001/

@endnode


@node Bugs "Bugs and problems"
@prev Thanks
@next Future

@{u}Bugs@{uu}

No bugs known, no Enforcer-hits found.

If you find any bugs, report them to @{" me " link Author}.


@{u}Problems@{uu}

The V43 picture.datatype seems to have problems with HAM pictures. These are loaded as normal 64 or 256 colored pictures.

Sometimes the machine crashes after creating very big icons with 256 colors and the option "SECONDIMAGE" set. I do not think this is a problem of @{b}DT2NI@{ub} but of newicon.library or Workbench.

@endnode


@node Future "Future"
@prev Bugs
@next History

There will be more versions of @{b}DT2NI@{ub}. Possible features are:


- GUI (this will really come!)

- Optimising the colortable

- Get the colors of a file

- Other aspect than 1:1

- Dithering

- No overwriting of existing (New-)icons

- More catalogs (if you send them to @{" me " link "Author"})

- ??? (this could be your @{" wish " link "Author"})

@endnode

@node Requirements "Requirements"
@prev Introduction
@next Usage

For using @{b}DT2NI@{ub} you will need:

  OS 3.0 or better

  @{" newicon.library " link "Thanks"}

  Picture-Datatypes


Recommended:

  picture.datatype V43 for pictures >8 bit

  Workbench with true- or high-color



@{b}DT2NI@{ub} was tested and developed on:

  Amiga 4000T, 68040/25MHz, CyberVision64

  OS 3.1

  newicon.library 39.1

  picture.datatype 43.759 (CyberGraphX)
  picture.datatype 43.24 (Picasso 96)
  picture.datatype 40.4

  datatypes.library 45.3

  CyberGraphX V3



It is reported that @{b}DT2NI@{ub} works with:

  OS 3.0

  CyberStorm 060

  EGSSpectrum with Picasso 96

  CyberVision64 with CyberGraphX V2

  Blizzard 1230-IV

@endnode


@node Introduction "Introduction"
@prev Copyright
@next Requirements

@{b}DT2NI@{ub} is a shell program which creates of all pictures it is able to load with @{" datatypes.library " link "Requirements"} @{" NewIcons " link "Requirements"}.

Besides this, you are able to define some @{" options " link "Usage"}, for example the size of icons.

The created icons can have upto 256 colors.

Of course, @{b}DT2NI@{ub} supports locale.library.

@endnode


@node Usage "Usage"
@prev Requirements
@next Author

@{b}DT2NI@{ub} supports the following arguments:


@{u}DIR/A@{uu}
Directory or file that will be scanned (required argument).


@{u}SIZE/N@{uu}
Size of the icons. This value must be between 25 and 92. Default is 40.


@{u}ALL/S@{uu}
Scan subdirectories too.


@{u}QUIET/S@{uu}
Suppress (nearly) all output.


@{u}FAST/S@{uu}
Use a faster (but not so nice-looking) scaling-algorithm.


@{u}NOSORT/S@{uu}
Do not sort directories when reading (scanning will be a little bit faster).


@{u}DEFTOOL/K@{uu}
Name of the default tool (default is "MultiView").


@{u}GREY/K/N@{uu}
Do not create icons in 256 colors but in grey. You may give one of the following values: 4, 8, 16, 32, 64, 128 or 256. Any other value will cause a fallback to 256 colors.


@{u}NOTOOLTYPES/S@{uu}
Do not write tooltypes with information about picture. If this argument is given @{b}DT2NI@{ub} will copy tooltypes of existing icons.


@{u}SECONDIMAGE/S@{uu}
A second (inverted) image to show the selected icon will be created.


@{u}NICONCOLORS/S@{uu}
With this option the standard colors on NewIcons (16 colors) will be used. This argument overwrites the option "GREY/K/N".


@{u}NOBACKFILL/S@{uu}
If this option is set there will be no black filling around the image and the icon need not to be square.

@endnode


